@rajeevfromca 

It appears the meaning has evolved in recent years. I grew up with the understanding that the distinct difference between being a gourmand vs a gourmet contributed to the negative meaning of gourmand. "Gourmand vs. Gourmet: A gourmand loves large amounts of good food, while a gourmet is more focused on the delicate, refined quality of food." The distinction between the two is how I remembered the meaning of gourmand. 

Now it seems that it is the link between the more positive gourmet that has "softened" the "old" meaning of gourmand, by this very association. So interesting how word meanings evolve and how we learn about the evolution!

